tp://www.imdb.com/title/tt0708495/","plotOutline":null},{"title":"Business as Usual","episodeID":"0708510","plot":["Quark must wrestle with his conscience when he becomes involved with arms merchants.::Taigan"],"imdbRating":7.3,"originalAirDate":"7 Apr. 1997","imdbURL":"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0708510/","plotOutline":null},{"title":"Ties of Blood and Water","episodeID":"0708651","plot":["When a Cardassian official (Lawrence Pressman), who thinks of Kira (Nana Visitor) as his daughter, is dying, he agrees to reveal all he knows to her. But the experience dredges up Kira's memories of her own father's (Thomas Kopache) death.::Taigan"],"imdbRating":7.2,"originalAirDate":"14 Apr. 1997","imdbURL":"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0708651/","plotOutline":null},{"title":"Ferengi Love Songs","episodeID":"0708541","plot":["Quark doesn't know whether to be panicked or overjoyed when he learns that his mother is the new lover of the Grand Nagus.::Taigan"],"imdbRating":6.7,"originalAirDate":"21 Apr. 1997","imdbURL":"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0708541/","plotOutline":null},{"title":"Soldiers of the Empire","episodeID":"0708603","plot":["Dax and Worf accompany Martok on his first command since being held by the Dominion. But the ship they are given hasn't seen victory in months and the crew is near mutinous.::Taigan"],"imdbRating":7.7,"originalAirDate":"28 Apr. 1997","imdbURL":"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0708603/","plotOutline":null},{"title":"Children of Time","episodeID":"0708516","plot":["The DS9 crew discovers a small colony on a remote world that was originally populated by them 200 years earlier due to a time-travel accident with the Defiant. The current colonists lives depend on making sure that accident happens again, even though they've now forwarned the crew that it will happen. Each crew member needs to decide if they are willing to give up their lives on DS9 in order to preserve the history of the colony.::Gholamite"],"imdbRating":7.9,"originalAirDate":"5 May 1997","imdbURL":"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0708516/","plotOutline":"The DS9 crew discovers a small colony on a remote world that was originally populated by them 200 years earlier due to a time-travel accident with the Defiant. The current colonists lives depend on making sure that accident happens again, even though they've now forwarned the crew that it will happen. Each crew member needs to decide if they are willing to give up their lives on DS9 in order to preserve the history of the colony."},{"title":"Blaze of Glory","episodeID":"0708506","plot":["Driven to desperation by the Dominion, the Maquis launch a massive bio-weapons strike towards Cardassia. Sisko must trust the traitor Eddington to try to stop them.::Taigan"],"imdbRating":7.6,"originalAirDate":"12 May 1997","imdbURL":"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0708506/","plotOutline":null},{"title":"Empok Nor","episodeID":"0708532","plot":["While salvaging components from DS9's sister station, the crew run afoul of a \"surprise\" left behind by the Cardassians.::Taigan"],"imdbRating":7.8,"originalAirDate":"19 May 1997","imdbURL":"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0708532/","plotOutline":null},{"title":"In the Cards","episodeID":"0708555","plot":["Jake and Nog go through hell and high water, from participating in an auction to dealing with the Dominion, to receiving a Willie Mays baseball card, all in order to cheer up the war-fatigued Captain Sisko.::UnforgivenSpaceCowboy"],"imdbRating":7.8,"originalAirDate":"9 Jun. 1997","imdbURL":"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0708555/","plotOutline":null},{"title":"Call to Arms","episodeID":"0708512","plot":["With the continuing battalions of Jem'Hadar entering the Alpha Quadrant in preparation for war, Sisko decides to mine the wormhole to prevent further troop movement. This provokes a confrontation between the Dominion and the Federation, forcing Sisko to abandon DS9.::Anonymous"],"imdbRating":9,"originalAirDate":"16 Jun. 1997","imdbURL":"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0708512/","plotOutline":"With the continuing battalions of Jem'Hadar entering the Alpha Quadrant in preparation for war, Sisko decides to mine the wormhole to prevent further troop movement. This provokes a confrontation between the Dominion and the Federation, forcing Sisko to abandon DS9."}],[{"title":"A Time to Stand","episodeID":"0708496","plot":["Borrowing a captured Jem'Hadar attack ship, Sisko and crew embark on a mission to destroy the hidden base where all of the ketracel-white is stored for the entire Alpha Quadrant.::Anonymous"],"imdbRating":8.5,"originalAirDate":"29 Sep. 1997","imdbURL":"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0708496/","plotOutline":null},{"title":"Rocks and Shoals","episodeID":"0708592","plot":["Sisko and his crew crash on a barren world when their commandeered Jem'Hadar ship is shot down. They encounter Jem'Hadar who crashed there earlier, and have taken Nog and Garak hostage in exchange for medical aid for their Vorta overseer.::LoboMensch","In the episode outline on the page it says the following: \"After a daring mission, the runabout crew is stranded on a remote planet, surrounded by a nebula, where Nog and Garrack are captured and offered as trade for the doctor to aid the enemy's injured Vorta\". Specifically, it is not a runabout, ie, \"runabout crew\", it was a captured Jem H'Dar warship, which was being used by the crew...::Tombo1984"],"imdbRating":8.6,"originalAirDate":"6 Oct. 1997","imdbURL":"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0708592/","plotOutline":"In the episode outline on the page it says the following: \"After a daring mission, the runabout crew is stranded on a remote planet, surrounded by a nebula, where Nog and Garrack are captured and offered as trade for the doctor to aid the enemy's injured Vorta\". Specifically, it is not a runabout, ie, \"runabout crew\", it was a captured Jem H'Dar warship, which was being used by the crew..."},{"title":"Sons and Daughters","episodeID":"0708604","plot":["Serving with his recruit son aboard a Klingon vessel, Worf finds his relationship with his son strained. Meanwhile, strained relationships abound on DS9 between Major Kira and Gul Dukat.::Moviedude1"],"imdbRating":7,"originalAirDate":"13 Oct. 1997","imdbURL":"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0708604/","plotOutline":null},{"title":"Behind the Lines","episodeID":"0708505","plot":["After forming an attack plan on the Dominion, Sisko relinquishes command of the Defiant to Dax after accepting a promotion. On DS9, the resistance faces discovery when Odo links with another changeling.::Moviedude1"],"imdbRating":7.9,"originalAirDate":"20 Oct. 1997","imdbURL":"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0708505/","plotOutline":null},{"title":"Favor the Bold","episodeID":"0708540","plot":["Sisko mounts an attack to re-take DS9, while Rom faces charges as an enemy of the Dominion state.::Moviedude1","After months of doing nothing but retreating from the Dominion, Sisko plans to launch a counterattack against the Dominion fleet occupying Deep Space 9/Terok Nor, with a simple goal - retake the station. However, Sisko finds out the minefield blocking the wormhole is about to be destroyed. Knowing that there are thousands of Jem'Hadar warships on the other side waiting to enter the Alpha Quadrant and annex every Federation planet, Sisko is forced to launch early, without the Ninth Fleet or the Klingons, and outnumbered two-to-one. Meanwhile, Rom is about to be executed for treason, with Odo too distracted by the Female Changeling to do anything.::movieguy3"],"imdbRating":8.6,"originalAirDate":"27 Oct. 1997","imdbURL":"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0708540/","plotOutline":"After months of doing nothing but retreating from the Dominion, Sisko plans to launch a counterattack against the Dominion fleet occupying Deep Space 9/Terok Nor, with a simple goal - retake the station. However, Sisko finds out the minefield blocking the wormhole is about to be destroyed. Knowing that there are thousands of Jem'Hadar warships on the other side waiting to enter the Alpha Quadrant and annex every Federation planet, Sisko is forced to launch early, without the Ninth Fleet or the Klingons, and outnumbered two-to-one. Meanwhile, Rom is about to be executed for treason, with Odo too distracted by the Female Changeling to do anything."},{"title":"Sacrifice of Angels","episodeID":"0708595","plot":["The Federation attacks DS9 in hopes of keeping the mine field at the wormhole intact, while the Dominion waits entrance to the Alpha Quadrant from the other side.::Moviedude1","Operation Return has begun. The goals: to get through the Dominion/Cardassian blockade; to retake Deep Space 9; and to stop the Dominion from destroying the minefield blocking the wormhole. But the blockade is barely budging, and back on Terok Nor (Deep Space 9), the resistance members are arrested, awaiting execution. Although Odo comes to his senses, are the resistance, and the Defiant, too late to stop the Dominion reinforcements?::movieguy3"],"imdbRating":8.9,"originalAirDate":"3 Nov. 1997","imdbURL":"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0708595/","plotOutline":"Operation Return has begun. The goals: to get through the Dominion/Cardassian blockade; to retake Deep Space 9; and to stop the Dominion from destroying the minefield blocking the wormhole. But the blockade is barely budging, and back on Terok Nor (Deep Space 9), the resistance members are arrested, awaiting execution. Although Odo comes to his senses, are the resistance, and the Defiant, too late to stop the Dominion reinforcements?"},{"title":"You Are Cordially Invited...","episodeID":"0708667","plot":["Suddenly desiring to wed within the week on DS9, Worf and Jadzia go through their own Klingon rituals: Worf on a four day bachelor party with the male members of the crew & Jadzia deals with her prospective mother-in-law, who totally opposes the idea of \"an alien\" marrying into her Klingon household.::Moviedude1"],"imdbRating":7.4,"originalAirDate":"10 Nov. 1997","imdbURL":"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0708667/","plotOutlin